history.content:
The CS conflict form needs to be manually done; getting that email is normal, as you won't be automatically allowed into the class.

Neither conflict form is particularly useful when there is no open space for the class. You would need to fill out the form such that someone looks at it when there is open space for you.
The CS conflict form needs to be manually done; getting that email is normal, as you won't be automatically allowed into the class.

children.subject: Same issue here. Anything I should do or just wait?

Filling out the time conflict form only means that if the time conflict form is processed when there is open space, you'll get in. It doesn't change the fact that the enrollment system will never automatically enroll you off the waitlist due to your conflict.
Yeah but the class was open when I was filling it out. The waitlist was just processed yesterday and that's when the remaining 150+ seats were filled.

It doesn't matter if the class was open when you filled it out, and it doesn't matter if the class is open when the waitlist is automatically processed.

It matters if the class was open when a human manually looks over your form.

Where did you access this form? I can't find it online anywhere and wasn't given the option to fill it out by CalCentral. I thought it was because I am waitlisted and not enrolled but now I see that isn't true. Somebody please respond

The SIS conflict override form only appears when you first try to enroll, and if there is open space in the class.

The CS conflict override form is at @5366.

If you are enrolled, then you don't need an override form; the override form is what is necessary to get enrolled in the first place.

The same thing happened to me but with CS C100. I was 10 on the waitlist before it was processed and the waitlist was over 200 so I was very confident I would get in the class. I got an email yesterday saying that because of a conflict I couldn't get off the waitlist. I had been filling out the CS Time Conflict form so I didn't think this would be a problem. Now the class has been filled and I'm still on the waitlist. I really needed to take this class and now I'm unsure what to do. Please let me know if there's anything else I can do to get into the class.

history.content:
I'm trying to enroll in a CS class with a time conflict. I filled out first the SIS form and then the CS Time Conflict Override form, and was able to add myself to the wait list. However, I recently received the following email.
---

You have NOT been enrolled from the wait list into the following class:

Class: COMPSCI   186 

Section: 001

Reason: Time conflict with another section.

You will remain on the wait list, and not be eligible to enroll during wait list processing, unless the time conflict is resolved.

Actions you can take:

  • Drop the time-conflicted class and reenroll into the dropped class to trigger receipt of time conflict override notification.

---
I'm confused because I already filled out the forms. Should I drop and re-add?
